 750 plaintiffs claim Johns Hopkins University approved and helped to plan the study from 1945 to 1956 in Guatemala that deliberately infected individuals with syphilis in order to test drugs and study the disease . 
  The lawsuit is seeking $1billion and includes victims and their families . 
  The study was run by Dr . 
  John Cutler and ran from 1945- 1956 . 
  It is estimated 700 people were infected with the disease in the experiment . 
  The few victims who are still alive were all children and orphans . 
  Some of the children were born blind and one was born without a brain . 
  The experiment was approved by Johns Hopkins officials . 
 